{"questionId":"27770","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><strong>In this question you will investigate series of the form</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munderover><mo largeop=\"true\">Σ</mo><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mi>n</mi></munderover><msup><mi>i</mi><mi>q</mi></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mn>1</mn><mi>q</mi></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>2</mn><mi>q</mi></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>3</mn><mi>q</mi></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>n</mi><mi>q</mi></msup></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>where&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>q</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math></p>\n<p><strong>and use various methods to find polynomials, in terms of</strong> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">n</mi></math>, <strong>for such series.</strong></p>\n<p>When&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>, the above series is arithmetic.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider the case when <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>You will now consider a method that can be generalized for all values of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>Consider the function <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>n</mi></msup><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>n</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mi>f</mi><mo>′</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math> and consider the following family of functions:</p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:210px;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>′</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math></p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:210px;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>'</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math></p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:210px;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>'</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math></p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:210px;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:210px;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mi>q</mi></msub><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><msub><mi>f</mi><mrow><mi>q</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>'</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>For <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>≠</mo><mn>1</mn></math>, show that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>n</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mi>f</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mfrac><mrow><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>n</mi></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>×</mo><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>M1</strong></em> for attempting to use the quotient or the product rule to find&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math>.</p>\n<p><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mfrac><mrow><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>n</mi></msup><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mfrac><mrow><mi>n</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>n</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>n</mi></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>n</mi></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong> </em>for any correct manipulation of the derivative that leads to the <em><strong>AG</strong></em>.</p>\n<p><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>n</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>attempts to form&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>n</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>n</mi></msup></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mi>n</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mi>n</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>n</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong>&nbsp;Award&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong>&nbsp;</em>for any correct manipulation of the derivative that leads to the&nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em>.</p>\n<p><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>n</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27770","referenceCode":"22N.3.AHL.TZ0.1f","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"For x≠1, show that f1x=nxn+2-n+1xn+1+xx-12.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"f","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.6—Differentiating polynomials n E Q. Chain, product and quotient rules"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}